WEBVTT

00:00.158 --> 00:02.031
<i>Previously on "Bitten"...</i>

00:02.254 --> 00:03.452
I'm surprised you haven't heard.

00:03.454 --> 00:04.406
I'm not the Sheriff anymore.

00:04.445 --> 00:06.773
I came to Bear Valley
looking for a quieter life

00:06.852 --> 00:08.585
and I realized I wasn't going
to get it being a cop.

00:08.587 --> 00:10.521
That is the one thing
that protects our kind.

00:10.523 --> 00:12.323
Humans can never know our secret.

00:12.325 --> 00:13.590
That's too great a risk!

00:13.592 --> 00:15.526
There were rumours thirty years ago

00:15.528 --> 00:18.362
of a baby girl, Sasha's child.

00:18.364 --> 00:19.863
- [Effort yell]
- Argh!

00:19.865 --> 00:21.432
KONSTANTIN: He's been
running away from the truth

00:21.434 --> 00:23.233
after causing your own mother's death.

00:23.235 --> 00:24.468
You killed her!

00:24.470 --> 00:26.136
She couldn't live after what you did!

00:26.138 --> 00:28.038
You showed her what you are!

00:28.040 --> 00:30.173
Your mother was my sister.

00:30.175 --> 00:31.442
Roman's daughter.

00:31.444 --> 00:32.709
SASHA: Alexei is about to go through

00:32.711 --> 00:34.478
one of the most painful and frightening

00:34.480 --> 00:36.446
experiences of his life.

00:36.448 --> 00:38.014
[Gasping, groaning]

00:38.016 --> 00:39.882
JEREMY: Let me deal with her.
You take Sasha.

00:39.884 --> 00:41.717
ELENA: Jeremy's focus has
been on bigger issues.

00:41.719 --> 00:43.186
I don't agree with all of his solutions.

00:43.188 --> 00:45.621
Get Katia away from
Stonehaven, someplace safe.

00:45.623 --> 00:47.123
<i>I think the Russians
are coming after her.</i>

00:47.125 --> 00:48.959
Hey, are you all right? What happened?

00:48.961 --> 00:50.160
What did you kill?

00:50.162 --> 00:51.995
I was a wolf!

00:51.997 --> 00:54.363
Alexei, this is human blood.

00:57.101 --> 01:00.273
[ ♪♪ ]

01:06.277 --> 01:07.643
[Cellphone ringing]

01:09.013 --> 01:10.512
[Sighing]

01:13.284 --> 01:14.950
Yeah, babe, what's wrong?

01:14.952 --> 01:16.685
WOMAN: [On phone] <i>You're not here.</i>

01:16.687 --> 01:19.721
MAN: Sonja, we agreed. Emergencies only.

01:19.723 --> 01:21.790
You know I'm roaming out here.

01:21.792 --> 01:23.459
SONJA: <i>Well, this</i> is <i> an emergency.</i>

01:24.996 --> 01:27.629
<i>I can't seem to keep my clothes on.</i>

01:27.631 --> 01:28.930
<i>Oops, there goes my bra...</i>

01:28.932 --> 01:31.065
All right, stop, just stop, okay?

01:31.067 --> 01:32.868
SONJA: <i>It's my mother. She's on me</i>

01:32.870 --> 01:34.936
<i>about what she should
bring to the BBQ tomorrow</i>

01:34.938 --> 01:36.471
<i>and she made some crack
about grilling deer.</i>

01:36.473 --> 01:37.806
Yeah well, maybe I should
bring this wolf urine.

01:37.808 --> 01:39.508
Does a good job of
keeping the deer away.

01:39.510 --> 01:41.209
Maybe it'll work on her.

01:41.211 --> 01:43.311
SONJA: <i>Why won't you
just let me tell her</i>

01:43.313 --> 01:45.079
<i>why you're really out there?</i>

01:45.081 --> 01:47.348
No, no, because then I'm going
to get her sad puppy dog eyes.

01:47.350 --> 01:48.983
And I've had enough of that.

01:48.985 --> 01:50.385
SONJA: <i>Okay, but you
will be back in time</i>

01:50.387 --> 01:51.685
<i>for this stupid thing, right?</i>

01:51.687 --> 01:53.254
TREVOR: Yeah, I'll be home.

01:53.256 --> 01:54.755
I don't want to be out here
when the hunters show.

01:54.757 --> 01:56.157
SONJA: <i>Well if they were more careful,</i>

01:56.159 --> 01:57.558
<i>you wouldn't have to do this every year.</i>

01:57.560 --> 01:58.792
TREVOR: Yeah, well, I want to.

01:58.794 --> 01:59.994
It keeps the deer away.

01:59.996 --> 02:02.162
And that's all that matters.

02:02.164 --> 02:04.999
SONJA: <i>I love you. I'll check
in with you in the morning.</i>

02:05.001 --> 02:07.034
All right. I love you too, babe.

02:07.036 --> 02:08.168
<i>Bye.</i>

02:10.639 --> 02:11.972
[Sighing]

02:15.244 --> 02:18.205
[ ♪♪ ]

02:20.000 --> 02:26.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:28.823 --> 02:30.223
[Crack of can opening]

02:30.225 --> 02:32.092
[ ♪♪ ]

02:34.729 --> 02:36.462
I miss you, Mike.

02:36.464 --> 02:38.370
[ ♪♪ ]

02:41.570 --> 02:42.969
[Crack of sticks]

02:42.971 --> 02:45.627
[ ♪♪ ]

02:55.716 --> 02:57.649
[Distant crack of sticks]

03:00.388 --> 03:02.121
[Rustling]

03:05.025 --> 03:06.157
Hello?

03:07.661 --> 03:09.761
[Crack of sticks]

03:09.763 --> 03:11.096
[Louder] Hello?

03:15.803 --> 03:18.269
[Panting, snarling]

03:19.573 --> 03:22.011
[ ♪♪ ]

03:51.846 --> 03:54.119
- sync and corrections by Caio -
- www.addic7ed.com -

03:56.612 --> 03:57.745
[Sighing]

03:59.749 --> 04:01.181
Hold still.

04:02.684 --> 04:04.751
I should be out there.

04:04.753 --> 04:06.686
Not Clay.

04:06.688 --> 04:08.354
Hold still!

04:08.356 --> 04:11.825
Or don't. Doesn't matter to me.

04:11.827 --> 04:13.760
[Phone notification chime]

04:17.932 --> 04:20.199
SASHA: Is that Clay?
Tell me where they are

04:20.201 --> 04:22.268
- and I'm going to go.
- I'm not done!

04:23.137 --> 04:26.192
[ ♪♪ ]

04:40.754 --> 04:44.256
- This is from the Russian wolf?
- Yeah.

04:44.258 --> 04:46.025
It's infected.

04:46.027 --> 04:48.227
It's okay.

04:48.229 --> 04:49.428
Elena, just leave it.

04:49.430 --> 04:51.262
- Leave it...
- Stop talking!

04:54.835 --> 04:56.167
[Thermometer beeps]

04:59.606 --> 05:00.739
This is bad.

05:00.741 --> 05:02.307
- Please...
- You need help. Quickly.

05:02.309 --> 05:04.609
No, I don't. Elena!

05:07.981 --> 05:09.247
MAN: [On phone] <i>Hello?</i>

05:09.249 --> 05:11.216
Anson. How quickly can
you get to Stonehaven?

05:11.218 --> 05:12.583
ANSON: <i>A few hours. What's up?</i>

05:12.585 --> 05:15.820
An infected wolf bite.
Maybe 36 hours ago.

05:15.822 --> 05:18.289
- ANSON: <i>I'm on my way.</i>
- Okay.

05:19.792 --> 05:21.525
You need to get up to the infirmary.

05:21.527 --> 05:23.327
You need to lie down and stay down.

05:23.329 --> 05:25.028
Just... just get me my phone.
I'm going to call Alexei,

05:25.030 --> 05:26.230
find where they are, okay?

05:26.232 --> 05:27.431
I cannot stay here doing nothing.

05:27.433 --> 05:28.766
What are you going to do?

05:28.768 --> 05:30.334
Haight is on his way here to help you.

05:30.336 --> 05:32.603
Until then, you're just
going to get worse.

05:32.605 --> 05:34.938
If you go out there, you're
just a liability to him.

05:34.940 --> 05:36.139
Don't say that.

05:36.141 --> 05:37.908
When you try and do things...

05:38.978 --> 05:40.377
things go wrong.

05:41.247 --> 05:44.020
[ ♪♪ ]

05:47.319 --> 05:49.353
Come on, Alexei. Anything.

05:49.355 --> 05:51.021
I can't remember any
of this, I don't know.

05:51.023 --> 05:53.490
You're going to have to try.
Just think, Alexei.

05:53.492 --> 05:55.525
Was it a male? Female?

05:55.527 --> 05:58.127
Near a house? On a road?

05:58.129 --> 06:00.797
Were there any other people
around when it happened?

06:00.799 --> 06:02.832
CLAY: Does any of this look familiar?

06:06.104 --> 06:07.437
That.

06:07.439 --> 06:09.372
I remember running past that.

06:13.077 --> 06:14.410
[Engine stops]

06:18.449 --> 06:21.417
- I need you to think.
- Which direction?

06:21.419 --> 06:23.619
I came through here so fast...

06:26.891 --> 06:29.391
I'd never run like that
before in my life.

06:31.161 --> 06:32.461
I'd...

06:32.463 --> 06:35.230
I'd never felt that strong before.

06:35.232 --> 06:36.665
I just...

06:36.667 --> 06:39.134
remember something running from me.

06:39.136 --> 06:40.469
[Eerie whoosh, rumble]

06:50.380 --> 06:51.779
[Sniffing]

06:51.781 --> 06:53.648
This is your fur.

06:55.018 --> 06:56.717
This way. Let's go.

06:59.389 --> 07:01.323
Alexei! Let's go.

07:06.963 --> 07:09.464
[Footsteps]

07:09.466 --> 07:11.732
NICK: [On phone] <i>I can turn
around, we can be there in...</i>

07:11.734 --> 07:13.133
<i>an hour and a half, tops.</i>

07:13.135 --> 07:14.769
Rachel isn't answering?

07:14.771 --> 07:17.104
- NICK: <i>No. But...</i>
- Go to Rachel's.

07:17.106 --> 07:20.274
- ELENA: <i>Is Katia within earshot?</i>
- She's in the restroom.

07:20.276 --> 07:22.609
ELENA: <i>Tell her Sasha
is resting upstairs.</i>

07:22.611 --> 07:25.279
But so that you know, Anson Haight
is on his way here to help.

07:25.281 --> 07:26.546
Okay. What about the others?

07:26.548 --> 07:28.248
ELENA: <i>Marsten and Cain are en route.</i>

07:28.250 --> 07:29.683
Clay is with Alexei.

07:29.685 --> 07:31.452
I'll get Jorge on to
tracking the Russians.

07:31.454 --> 07:34.955
<i>Once we know where they went,
we can make a plan, but I...</i>

07:34.957 --> 07:37.491
I'm more concerned about Jeremy.

07:37.493 --> 07:39.860
So no one is with him?

07:39.862 --> 07:41.628
He told me he wants to be alone.

07:41.630 --> 07:44.798
Did Morgan see Alexei change?

07:44.800 --> 07:47.701
If Jeremy is convinced that
she didn't see him change,

07:47.703 --> 07:50.436
if he can get her out of
that room alive, he will.

07:50.438 --> 07:53.373
You really think he'll give
her the benefit of the doubt?

07:54.775 --> 07:57.143
I don't know, Nick.

07:59.871 --> 08:03.121
[ ♪♪ ]

08:07.222 --> 08:09.955
ALEXEI: [Groaning, yelling]

08:11.261 --> 08:14.675
[ ♪♪ ]

08:20.100 --> 08:21.433
[Sighing]

08:22.403 --> 08:23.736
[Coughing]

08:25.139 --> 08:26.471
[Sharp intake of breath]

08:27.541 --> 08:28.873
[Groaning]

08:31.345 --> 08:32.977
What happened?

08:32.979 --> 08:35.880
I wrapped your leg wound
to stop the bleeding.

08:35.881 --> 08:38.716
- Ahh...
- You took a terrible blow to your head.

08:43.389 --> 08:46.024
I had the strangest dream.

08:47.093 --> 08:48.560
You had a dream?

08:48.562 --> 08:49.861
What kind of dream?

08:49.863 --> 08:53.330
Contorted animal or something.

08:53.332 --> 08:55.066
What kind of animal?

08:55.068 --> 08:57.035
I don't even know...

08:57.037 --> 09:00.037
[Groaning] Must be from this.

09:00.039 --> 09:01.439
[Water pouring]

09:01.441 --> 09:03.307
A blow like that...

09:03.309 --> 09:06.743
can make a person hallucinate
the strangest things.

09:11.384 --> 09:12.716
What am I...

09:14.086 --> 09:15.418
How did I get here?

09:16.521 --> 09:18.154
Everything is fine.

09:18.156 --> 09:19.489
I'm hurt.

09:20.593 --> 09:21.992
Everything is fine, Karen.

09:21.994 --> 09:24.094
Here. Acetaminophen.

09:24.096 --> 09:27.297
It's all I have, but it'll
help with the pain.

09:27.299 --> 09:29.700
You're going to feel
dazed for a little bit.

09:34.239 --> 09:37.395
[ ♪♪ ]

09:47.051 --> 09:48.851
Is an ambulance coming?

09:51.589 --> 09:53.656
We need to talk first.

09:54.659 --> 09:55.992
I need to go.

09:58.663 --> 10:00.896
That's not a good idea.

10:00.898 --> 10:02.098
Not yet.

10:02.100 --> 10:04.233
[ ♪♪ ]

10:05.670 --> 10:10.305
[ ♪♪ ]

10:11.951 --> 10:14.218
Hold on, I remember this.

10:14.220 --> 10:16.154
I remember this truck.

10:16.428 --> 10:18.295
Maybe I didn't bite him.

10:18.297 --> 10:19.263
Maybe I just clawed him.

10:19.381 --> 10:21.915
CLAY: Either way, we need to find him.

10:22.732 --> 10:23.931
There's no body.

10:23.933 --> 10:25.166
Think! What happened?

10:25.168 --> 10:26.934
I don't know! What did I do...

10:29.505 --> 10:32.072
[Panting]

10:35.878 --> 10:37.444
Trevor Resayas.

10:39.148 --> 10:42.616
The guy <i> you attacked</i> is
named Trevor Resayas.

10:42.772 --> 10:44.405
I need you to wrap your
head around the fact

10:44.429 --> 10:45.962
that there is a human
out there, somewhere,

10:45.964 --> 10:48.530
possibly alive, possibly changing.

10:48.532 --> 10:50.132
- No...
- Hey! Alexei!

10:50.134 --> 10:51.968
You can't shut down on me.

10:51.970 --> 10:53.535
We have to find him.

10:58.609 --> 11:00.042
There's only one set of tracks in.

11:00.044 --> 11:02.311
That's good, no one drove him out.

11:07.518 --> 11:08.650
Wolf urine?

11:09.820 --> 11:11.052
People use it in Dawson

11:11.054 --> 11:12.988
to keep deer out of their gardens.

11:18.662 --> 11:20.695
Deer hunting season starts tomorrow.

11:20.697 --> 11:23.131
Maybe he's some sort of an activist.

11:23.133 --> 11:24.599
If he's experienced in the woods,

11:24.601 --> 11:26.667
he'll know how to find
his way out of here.

11:30.673 --> 11:32.007
[Growling]

11:32.876 --> 11:34.409
He had gasoline.

11:37.881 --> 11:42.082
He spilled gas on me.
That's why I smelled of it.

11:42.084 --> 11:44.018
It tasted bitter.

11:44.020 --> 11:47.588
Stung in my mouth. It made me stop.

11:47.590 --> 11:50.257
But before the gas, I tasted...

11:51.928 --> 11:53.127
...blood.

11:53.129 --> 11:56.063
[Growling]

11:58.528 --> 11:59.861
I bit him.

12:01.564 --> 12:03.197
I know I bit him.

12:06.436 --> 12:07.802
[Cellphone ringing]

12:11.707 --> 12:14.275
[Ringing continues]

12:25.554 --> 12:26.887
Let's go.

12:34.296 --> 12:36.429
ELENA: I've got the map.

12:36.431 --> 12:38.331
If Roman crossed at
Niagara, then we'll see

12:38.333 --> 12:40.534
if we can track them
through Southern Ontario.

12:42.091 --> 12:43.457
Thanks, Jorge.

12:44.327 --> 12:45.859
Hop on the next flight out.

12:45.861 --> 12:48.028
We're going to need you here.

12:49.232 --> 12:50.364
[Beep]

12:51.767 --> 12:52.966
What are you doing up?

12:52.968 --> 12:54.635
SASHA: Is this about Roman?

12:54.637 --> 12:56.103
He's in Canada, huh?

12:56.105 --> 12:57.671
Wh... [Coughing] Where?

12:57.673 --> 12:58.872
Sit down.

12:58.874 --> 13:00.207
I cannot sleep, okay?

13:00.209 --> 13:02.609
Not with everything in disarray.

13:02.611 --> 13:03.810
[Coughing]

13:03.812 --> 13:05.478
Sit. Down.

13:05.480 --> 13:07.147
[Sighing, coughing]

13:09.885 --> 13:11.084
[Water trickling]

13:11.086 --> 13:13.286
You're angry with me, huh?

13:13.288 --> 13:14.420
[Clatter]

13:15.857 --> 13:18.625
You don't want to get into
this with me right now.

13:18.627 --> 13:19.892
SASHA: I do.

13:19.894 --> 13:22.629
No, you don't.

13:22.631 --> 13:24.364
Trust me, the things
that I'm angry about,

13:24.366 --> 13:25.831
they're not going anywhere.

13:25.833 --> 13:27.833
I'm here, now.

13:27.835 --> 13:29.168
Be honest with me.

13:30.505 --> 13:32.271
Be honest with you?

13:32.273 --> 13:33.538
You weren't honest with me.

13:33.540 --> 13:36.275
You came down here with
only half the story.

13:36.277 --> 13:39.011
"I'm your father. Here
are your siblings."

13:41.849 --> 13:44.616
All I ever wanted was a family.

13:44.618 --> 13:45.985
But every single time,

13:45.987 --> 13:47.186
it's like everyone only puts forward

13:47.188 --> 13:50.522
the best versions of themselves.

13:50.524 --> 13:53.224
You hide the part that
will make me walk away.

13:54.295 --> 13:55.427
Everyone?

13:57.431 --> 13:58.563
You.

13:59.833 --> 14:02.000
But this has happened to you before.

14:06.807 --> 14:08.139
Yes.

14:09.509 --> 14:11.375
Right where you're sitting.

14:15.615 --> 14:19.750
When Clay bit me in, he
didn't tell me what he was.

14:19.752 --> 14:23.120
He was just hoping to save me.

14:23.122 --> 14:25.556
And Jeremy was...

14:25.558 --> 14:28.626
convinced that I'd seen him change.

14:28.628 --> 14:30.027
If he thought that...

14:33.700 --> 14:35.299
[Shaky exhale]

14:35.301 --> 14:37.634
He was going to kill me.

14:38.704 --> 14:41.642
[ ♪♪ ]

14:50.316 --> 14:52.682
Your leg is stable.

14:52.684 --> 14:55.218
It's going to be fine.

14:58.156 --> 14:59.823
I don't want to frighten you.

14:59.825 --> 15:01.658
Then tell me why I'm still here.

15:01.660 --> 15:04.627
I need to understand what
you're doing, Karen.

15:11.602 --> 15:13.669
Why are you here?

15:13.671 --> 15:15.437
The Russians.

15:15.439 --> 15:18.407
I saw them in town.
Something seemed off.

15:18.409 --> 15:21.077
I followed them here, I saw your car.

15:21.079 --> 15:23.279
I was concerned for your safety.

15:23.281 --> 15:24.613
You saw them outside.

15:26.317 --> 15:29.117
Look Jeremy, whatever happened here...

15:29.119 --> 15:32.320
I can help. Pull some strings.

15:32.322 --> 15:34.390
I haven't been away from
the uniform that long.

15:34.392 --> 15:36.124
Did you report them? The Russians?

15:36.126 --> 15:37.659
I heard you. I thought
you were in trouble.

15:37.661 --> 15:40.529
So I came up here. I'm on your side.

15:42.165 --> 15:44.232
I want to believe you, Karen.

15:44.234 --> 15:46.467
I have friends in the FBI.

15:46.469 --> 15:49.304
We can get you out of this, Jeremy.

15:53.143 --> 15:54.475
I can help.

15:55.545 --> 15:57.445
Listen to me.

15:57.447 --> 16:00.347
The only way that we're
going to get out of this

16:00.349 --> 16:03.418
is if you let me help you.

16:09.726 --> 16:11.726
SASHA: I'll tell you everything.

16:14.163 --> 16:16.063
You can't hide the bad.

16:16.065 --> 16:17.898
The bad is the part that I need to know.

16:17.900 --> 16:20.634
It's the part that lets me
decide if I want any of this.

16:20.636 --> 16:23.437
I don't want to hurt you anymore.

16:23.439 --> 16:25.839
"Anymore"...

16:25.841 --> 16:30.377
Why wouldn't you just tell
me that I'm a Navikev?

16:30.379 --> 16:32.112
How did I find out?

16:32.114 --> 16:33.379
Should've been from you but instead,

16:33.381 --> 16:35.682
Konstantin told me.

16:35.684 --> 16:38.752
Konstantin, who's apparently my uncle.

16:38.754 --> 16:41.955
He's the one that told me the truth,

16:41.957 --> 16:43.757
just before he tried to kill me.

16:43.759 --> 16:44.958
I'm sorry, Elena.

16:44.960 --> 16:46.560
I'm not done.

16:53.568 --> 16:54.700
My mother.

16:59.040 --> 17:01.074
Did you kill her?

17:02.877 --> 17:05.979
[ ♪♪ ]

17:17.892 --> 17:20.626
[ ♪♪ ]

17:20.627 --> 17:21.760
Yes.

17:22.625 --> 17:24.358
In a way, I did.

17:34.936 --> 17:36.069
Hey.

17:42.260 --> 17:44.927
This guy's a fighter. He's
pushing to get out of the woods.

17:46.385 --> 17:49.053
Well you know, if he got
this far, maybe he survived.

17:49.055 --> 17:51.055
Maybe I didn't kill him.

17:51.057 --> 17:53.490
If he survived, that's worse.

17:53.492 --> 17:56.460
He's out there somewhere,
in pain, confused.

17:56.462 --> 18:00.063
The wolf is making its
way through his blood.

18:00.065 --> 18:02.366
He gets to a hospital,
starts changing...

18:02.368 --> 18:04.968
We're done, Alexei.

18:04.970 --> 18:06.202
The secret's blown,

18:06.204 --> 18:07.504
do you understand what that means?

18:07.506 --> 18:09.740
If we find him, and he's alive,

18:09.742 --> 18:11.975
maybe there's some
sort of middle ground.

18:11.977 --> 18:13.709
Maybe we can bring him
in, we can train him.

18:13.711 --> 18:15.145
There's no middle ground, Alexei.

18:15.147 --> 18:16.679
I don't make these rules.

18:16.681 --> 18:18.148
So break them.

18:20.118 --> 18:22.886
Trevor Resayas already has a life.

18:22.888 --> 18:25.388
A woman who's calling him.

18:25.390 --> 18:27.423
He finds out he's about
to become a werewolf?

18:27.425 --> 18:29.858
There's little chance he's going
to want to learn to live like us

18:29.860 --> 18:32.127
and give up everything he loves.

18:32.129 --> 18:33.763
We don't know him.

18:33.765 --> 18:35.898
We don't know the people who know him.
It's too risky.

18:35.900 --> 18:37.800
So he's dead either way.

18:37.802 --> 18:39.902
Why not let him choose?

18:39.904 --> 18:41.136
You know, maybe you're wrong.

18:41.138 --> 18:42.971
Maybe this whole system
of rules is wrong.

18:42.973 --> 18:44.273
No.

18:44.275 --> 18:48.177
The only reason this works, our lives,

18:48.179 --> 18:50.112
is because we have to rely on each other

18:50.114 --> 18:52.815
to keep the secret.

18:53.613 --> 18:56.832
[ ♪♪ ]

19:10.967 --> 19:15.370
I see her face in yours.

19:15.372 --> 19:18.005
The first time I saw you,

19:18.007 --> 19:19.340
I saw her.

19:20.676 --> 19:23.010
She was stubborn too, you
know, like you. But...

19:23.012 --> 19:25.146
No, not stubborn. Um...

19:26.816 --> 19:28.149
Defiant.

19:30.186 --> 19:33.387
I have nothing to go on
except what you tell me.

19:35.257 --> 19:37.825
Right now, I think that
you murdered my mother.

19:37.827 --> 19:39.426
No...

19:39.428 --> 19:41.495
Oh, I loved your mother.

19:42.598 --> 19:46.333
And Roman loved your grandmother.

19:46.335 --> 19:47.534
But when your mother was born,

19:47.536 --> 19:50.270
he distanced himself from them,

19:50.272 --> 19:51.838
but made sure they were provided for.

19:51.840 --> 19:54.807
He bought them a house in the country.

19:54.809 --> 19:57.177
When your grandmother died,

19:57.179 --> 20:00.247
Roman felt it was too
dangerous for him to go,

20:00.249 --> 20:02.815
he might want to meet his daughter,

20:02.817 --> 20:05.118
so he sent me to check in,

20:05.120 --> 20:06.386
just to make sure she was okay,

20:06.388 --> 20:08.521
and at want for nothing.

20:08.523 --> 20:12.324
It started out as an obligation.

20:12.326 --> 20:15.194
I didn't expect to fall in love.

20:16.446 --> 20:19.930
[ ♪♪ ]

20:22.270 --> 20:24.270
ELENA: What was she like?

20:27.774 --> 20:29.440
Natalya.

20:32.545 --> 20:35.046
She was...

20:35.048 --> 20:37.382
everything.

20:37.384 --> 20:38.649
The first time I saw her,

20:38.651 --> 20:40.251
she was in the graveyard in the town,

20:40.253 --> 20:41.519
she was putting flowers

20:41.521 --> 20:44.855
on your grandmother's grave.

20:44.857 --> 20:46.590
I saw her, and...

20:46.592 --> 20:50.294
I could not help myself,
I had to speak to her.

20:50.296 --> 20:51.662
And so I lied,

20:51.664 --> 20:53.864
I told her my mother
was buried there, too.

20:53.866 --> 20:57.067
The next day I took her for coffee.

20:57.069 --> 20:59.537
I took her hand.

20:59.539 --> 21:02.572
And I never wanted to let go.

21:02.574 --> 21:05.175
She had no idea who you were?

21:05.177 --> 21:07.277
No...

21:07.279 --> 21:08.478
Not at first.

21:08.480 --> 21:10.847
But I couldn't stay away.

21:12.084 --> 21:14.384
And soon, I was...

21:14.386 --> 21:16.519
seeing her every moment that I could.

21:16.521 --> 21:19.088
All the while, I lying to Roman.

21:19.090 --> 21:20.457
You know, I was hiding.

21:20.459 --> 21:24.160
Torn between my Alpha and my love.

21:24.162 --> 21:27.430
My duty and my dream.

21:29.634 --> 21:32.168
I couldn't bear to lie to her anymore.

21:33.904 --> 21:37.206
Not after I found out she
was pregnant with you.

21:38.943 --> 21:41.877
I loved her too much.

21:41.879 --> 21:43.312
So you told her...

21:43.314 --> 21:44.880
...Who I was.

21:44.882 --> 21:49.018
Someone sent by her father
to check in on her.

21:49.020 --> 21:50.619
And what I was.

21:51.689 --> 21:53.288
A monster.

21:56.994 --> 21:58.827
But a monster who loved her.

21:59.697 --> 22:01.329
I've fought all my life.

22:01.331 --> 22:02.931
I've killed men, even.

22:02.933 --> 22:04.733
But the two of you...

22:04.735 --> 22:07.735
you made me feel stronger
than I'd ever felt before.

22:09.805 --> 22:13.047
[ ♪♪ ]

22:16.113 --> 22:18.646
[Cellphone ringing]

22:21.284 --> 22:23.684
[Ringing continues]

22:23.686 --> 22:24.819
[Beep]

22:26.322 --> 22:28.823
But when you're a wolf,

22:28.825 --> 22:31.592
how do you know what's
wrong and what's right?

22:32.461 --> 22:33.694
Humans will run.

22:33.696 --> 22:35.763
The wolf instinct is to chase.

22:35.765 --> 22:39.166
You need to train that instinct out.

22:39.168 --> 22:40.700
But how do you do that?

22:40.702 --> 22:42.702
You tap into the part of
you that's still human.

22:42.704 --> 22:45.339
You remain aware that
everyone has a life.

22:45.341 --> 22:46.907
When you pass someone on the street,

22:46.909 --> 22:49.109
they have hopes, dreams

22:49.111 --> 22:50.577
fears, regrets.

22:50.579 --> 22:53.447
They want to walk the Great Wall.

22:53.449 --> 22:54.714
Learn to swim.

22:54.716 --> 22:58.084
Run a marathon. Beat cancer.

22:58.086 --> 23:00.687
They're thinking about what's
in the freezer for dinner,

23:00.689 --> 23:02.989
or how to tell someone they're sorry.

23:02.991 --> 23:06.626
They love and they hurt and they are.

23:06.628 --> 23:08.494
Then there's a ripple effect.

23:08.496 --> 23:10.063
Trevor's friends.

23:10.065 --> 23:11.631
Sonja.

23:11.633 --> 23:13.832
His mother. Maybe he has kids.

23:13.834 --> 23:16.436
People who love him.
People who rely on him.

23:16.438 --> 23:18.104
Their lives are forever changed

23:18.106 --> 23:20.039
by what you've done.

23:21.976 --> 23:26.212
The red-eyed wolf who killed my mother?

23:26.214 --> 23:28.548
He didn't care about any of that.

23:28.550 --> 23:30.983
Neither did the wolf who killed mine.

23:32.053 --> 23:34.905
[ ♪♪ ]

23:46.666 --> 23:47.999
[ ♪♪ ]

23:48.001 --> 23:49.334
And her death?

23:52.139 --> 23:54.473
I shared our secret.

23:54.475 --> 23:56.674
I broke the rules.

23:56.676 --> 23:59.377
I let your mother see me change.

24:01.448 --> 24:03.648
And she loved me anyway.

24:05.451 --> 24:07.719
But there's no going back from that.

24:07.721 --> 24:11.355
On the day she died,
everything was calm.

24:11.357 --> 24:13.390
[Baby fussing]

24:13.392 --> 24:16.127
[ ♪♪ ]

24:16.129 --> 24:18.262
I'd taken you for a walk in the woods.

24:18.264 --> 24:20.864
[Eerie music]

24:21.983 --> 24:24.819
[ ♪♪ ]

24:30.109 --> 24:32.143
[Yelping, gasping]

24:33.003 --> 24:35.597
[ ♪♪ ]

24:37.349 --> 24:39.616
When I came back,

24:39.618 --> 24:41.317
she was dead.

24:42.443 --> 24:45.162
[ ♪♪ ]

24:50.929 --> 24:54.730
Roman waited for me, to kill me.

24:56.137 --> 24:58.121
[ ♪♪ ]

25:08.512 --> 25:10.512
How did Roman find out?

25:10.514 --> 25:11.747
I don't know...

25:11.749 --> 25:13.149
I've tried to piece that together

25:13.151 --> 25:14.383
since her death.

25:14.385 --> 25:16.318
It's a question that haunts me

25:16.320 --> 25:18.821
every waking moment.

25:18.823 --> 25:20.622
I should have fought him,

25:20.624 --> 25:22.158
but I didn't.

25:22.160 --> 25:25.026
I should have gone to her,

25:25.028 --> 25:27.095
but I didn't.

25:27.097 --> 25:29.331
I...

25:29.333 --> 25:32.067
I had to get you away.

25:32.069 --> 25:33.435
So I ran.

25:33.437 --> 25:35.136
You had me.

25:36.674 --> 25:38.173
How did we get separated?

25:38.175 --> 25:40.275
I knew Roman was going to come after me.

25:40.277 --> 25:42.610
It was not safe. I, um...

25:43.479 --> 25:46.214
I left you at a small hospital.

25:46.216 --> 25:48.482
It was run by Canadian
volunteers, but...

25:48.484 --> 25:49.918
A Russian nurse, she promised me

25:49.920 --> 25:51.886
that she would keep you safe.

25:51.888 --> 25:55.156
When I circled back, months later...

25:55.158 --> 25:56.791
you were gone.

25:56.793 --> 25:58.192
Taken to Canada by the couple

25:58.194 --> 26:00.661
that would become the
parents that you knew.

26:00.663 --> 26:04.064
I thought that was for the best.

26:04.066 --> 26:07.167
So you got away...

26:07.169 --> 26:08.669
and still, you gave me up?

26:08.671 --> 26:10.371
I did it to protect you.

26:10.373 --> 26:12.707
You thought I was a liability.

26:17.412 --> 26:20.413
Thirty years, I have hated myself

26:20.415 --> 26:21.815
for what I did.

26:21.817 --> 26:25.452
So I understand if you do, as well.

26:25.454 --> 26:27.554
For what I did to you.

26:27.556 --> 26:29.957
For what happened to her.

26:33.995 --> 26:35.729
I'm sorry.

26:40.736 --> 26:42.469
Roman killed her.

26:43.972 --> 26:46.172
Not you.

26:46.174 --> 26:48.540
Her death was his fault.

26:50.111 --> 26:51.543
Yes, and no.

26:51.545 --> 26:53.579
For him, he had no choice.

26:53.581 --> 26:56.315
I broke the rules.

26:56.317 --> 26:59.652
Natalya should never
have known what I was.

26:59.654 --> 27:02.054
I thought love was enough.

27:02.056 --> 27:04.189
This secret...

27:04.191 --> 27:07.426
It doesn't protect us.

27:07.428 --> 27:08.860
It kills us.

27:08.862 --> 27:11.029
But what can we do?

27:11.031 --> 27:12.498
There are rules in this world,

27:12.500 --> 27:14.166
however unfair they may seem

27:14.168 --> 27:15.367
to you and me.

27:15.369 --> 27:17.202
She was innocent.

27:17.204 --> 27:19.505
So were you.

27:19.507 --> 27:21.539
If Jeremy was about to kill you,

27:21.541 --> 27:23.308
it wasn't because of you.

27:23.310 --> 27:25.143
Your mother didn't do anything wrong,

27:25.145 --> 27:26.544
neither did you.

27:26.546 --> 27:28.079
Exactly.

27:29.382 --> 27:31.082
Yet he was going to killed me.

27:31.084 --> 27:33.919
Jeremy would have lived with your death

27:33.921 --> 27:36.887
the same way I live with your mother's.

27:39.225 --> 27:41.759
He didn't even know me.

27:42.862 --> 27:46.163
I was just a girl, in love.

27:48.802 --> 27:50.000
And I was nervous to meet him.

27:50.002 --> 27:52.136
And he was going to kill me.

27:52.138 --> 27:53.503
Even if he did know,

27:53.505 --> 27:54.905
it still wouldn't matter.

27:54.907 --> 27:56.573
The rules are in place

27:56.575 --> 27:58.843
and he believes in those rules.

27:58.845 --> 28:00.177
Your biology saved you,

28:00.179 --> 28:03.413
it gave him the chance to know you,

28:03.415 --> 28:05.316
to love you.

28:05.318 --> 28:08.518
He carries the guilt
of what he almost did.

28:08.520 --> 28:11.154
He wears it in his heart

28:11.156 --> 28:14.725
and he wears it in his eyes.

28:14.727 --> 28:18.127
See your way to forgive him.

28:18.129 --> 28:20.864
Everything he does is to protect you.

28:20.866 --> 28:24.401
Everything that he does
is to protect the Pack.

28:24.403 --> 28:25.736
No.

28:27.038 --> 28:28.171
It's you.

28:31.609 --> 28:34.077
You are the heart of this Pack.

28:35.881 --> 28:38.982
Without you, there is nothing.

28:40.069 --> 28:42.600
[ ♪♪ ]

28:51.789 --> 28:55.489
So how are you helping me get out
of this? Calling an ambulance?

28:57.586 --> 29:00.519
You seemed so happy when
you said you retired.

29:00.521 --> 29:02.222
Remember you told me you
were ready to settle down?

29:02.224 --> 29:03.442
A quiet life?

29:03.466 --> 29:05.590
Like I say, I was concerned
for your safety.

29:05.724 --> 29:07.824
I heard the fighting. I saw your car.

29:07.826 --> 29:09.476
So once a cop, always a cop?

29:09.539 --> 29:11.672
I came here because of you.

29:11.674 --> 29:13.074
But you first came here

29:13.076 --> 29:14.976
because you were interested
in the Russians.

29:14.978 --> 29:16.610
Your instincts were right.

29:16.612 --> 29:18.879
They were here to kill someone.

29:18.881 --> 29:19.880
Not you?

29:19.882 --> 29:22.650
No. Actually, I don't know.

29:23.786 --> 29:25.720
Some old family history.

29:25.722 --> 29:26.920
I was trying to fix it.

29:26.922 --> 29:29.923
A vendetta between two families, and...

29:29.925 --> 29:31.359
I couldn't make it right.

29:31.361 --> 29:32.759
Brokering the peace today...

29:32.761 --> 29:34.661
that was your responsibility?

29:34.663 --> 29:38.531
It's always my responsibility.

29:38.533 --> 29:40.167
It falls on me.

29:42.371 --> 29:43.570
When you were a Sheriff,

29:43.572 --> 29:46.706
was there ever... a moment

29:46.708 --> 29:49.609
even just for a second,

29:49.611 --> 29:51.177
when you wished that you could hand off

29:51.179 --> 29:52.579
some of that responsibility?

29:52.581 --> 29:53.980
Just a little piece of your job

29:53.982 --> 29:56.483
so someone else would do the work?

29:56.485 --> 29:57.751
You met my Deputy.

29:57.753 --> 29:59.352
I could barely trust him
with a lunch order.

29:59.354 --> 30:01.521
BOTH: [Chuckling]

30:03.425 --> 30:05.624
Know what, okay...

30:05.626 --> 30:07.659
I have a sister. Lucy.

30:07.661 --> 30:09.128
She trusts implicitly.

30:09.130 --> 30:11.463
She was always dating the wrong guy,

30:11.465 --> 30:12.731
and giving them her PIN number

30:12.733 --> 30:15.434
and then calling me
when things fell apart.

30:15.436 --> 30:17.236
I was always there for her, but...

30:17.238 --> 30:20.206
my advice never really took.

30:20.208 --> 30:22.908
When I rose up through
the ranks and got busy,

30:22.910 --> 30:25.377
and her life happened
and before I knew it,

30:25.379 --> 30:26.712
she met Josh.

30:26.714 --> 30:28.447
He's one of the good ones.

30:28.449 --> 30:31.583
Whirlwind romance, down on one knee...

30:34.221 --> 30:36.187
I'm her only sister.

30:36.189 --> 30:38.323
I was the maid of honour.

30:38.325 --> 30:40.258
The morning of her wedding,

30:40.260 --> 30:42.060
I got a call.

30:42.062 --> 30:44.329
I was still on the force in Baltimore.

30:44.331 --> 30:45.663
You had to answer the call.

30:45.665 --> 30:47.865
I had been trying to solve that case

30:47.867 --> 30:49.467
for years.

30:49.469 --> 30:51.369
Domestic homicide.

30:51.371 --> 30:52.570
A witness came forward.

30:52.572 --> 30:53.771
He was going to be deported,

30:53.773 --> 30:55.440
we had the tiniest
window of opportunity,

30:55.442 --> 30:56.808
so I took it.

30:56.810 --> 30:58.208
It was my responsibility.

30:58.210 --> 30:59.610
That case wasn't going
to get solved otherwise.

30:59.612 --> 31:01.612
I had <i> years...</i>

31:01.614 --> 31:03.848
to make it up to my sister.

31:05.618 --> 31:07.017
But how did she feel?

31:07.019 --> 31:08.152
Huh...

31:10.423 --> 31:12.689
I'd love to talk to her about it.

31:12.691 --> 31:15.625
If she'd take my calls.

31:15.627 --> 31:18.562
But 10 years later, she still won't.

31:18.564 --> 31:20.164
You made a tough choice.

31:21.400 --> 31:22.967
I took an oath.

31:24.236 --> 31:26.003
To me, there was no choice.

31:29.675 --> 31:31.641
But I was wrong.

31:33.044 --> 31:35.178
I should've been there for her.

31:36.782 --> 31:38.348
That witness could've been interviewed

31:38.350 --> 31:39.983
by my partner.

31:41.186 --> 31:45.021
It seemed so important to
me at the time, and...

31:47.525 --> 31:50.593
I have a niece I've never met.

31:52.563 --> 31:54.998
It's more important.

31:55.967 --> 31:57.967
Family, that's what matters.

32:04.375 --> 32:07.209
Everything that I do, I
do to protect my family.

32:08.946 --> 32:11.013
The Russian, Roman Navikev,

32:11.015 --> 32:13.048
he wanted to kill the
other man that was here,

32:13.050 --> 32:15.117
it's an obsession about an old vendetta.

32:15.119 --> 32:17.685
But he... he also...

32:17.687 --> 32:19.721
wants to kill a member of my family.

32:19.723 --> 32:21.490
And I'm just trying to prevent that.

32:21.492 --> 32:23.691
And things got violent, and
that's when you walked in.

32:23.693 --> 32:25.593
And made things worse.

32:26.763 --> 32:29.164
I think that we can make this better.

32:32.202 --> 32:34.068
Could you just walk away from this?

32:34.070 --> 32:35.269
From what I know?

32:35.271 --> 32:37.005
Yeah, from what you saw.

32:37.007 --> 32:38.406
From what happened to you.

32:38.408 --> 32:40.441
Can you just understand

32:40.443 --> 32:43.377
that I am a man trying
to protect his family.

32:43.379 --> 32:45.713
So I just turn a blind eye?

32:45.715 --> 32:47.715
These are very bad people.

32:47.717 --> 32:48.983
And you don't want help?

32:48.985 --> 32:51.285
That would just make
things infinitely worse,

32:51.287 --> 32:52.753
trust me.

32:54.290 --> 32:55.889
Can you trust me?

32:55.891 --> 32:57.691
I want to be able to trust you.

32:57.693 --> 32:59.026
I want to trust that

32:59.028 --> 33:00.461
you are just going to
walk away from here

33:00.463 --> 33:03.030
and find that quiet life.

33:03.032 --> 33:06.133
I learned too late from my mistakes.

33:06.135 --> 33:08.168
I lost my sister.

33:09.337 --> 33:11.805
I do want a quiet life.

33:14.910 --> 33:16.043
So...

33:17.713 --> 33:19.913
what happened today was...

33:19.915 --> 33:22.282
I was... pruning my hedges

33:22.284 --> 33:24.184
and I fell off my ladder.

33:26.621 --> 33:27.954
Yes.

33:29.991 --> 33:32.725
And... we walk out that door together?

33:35.597 --> 33:37.263
Yes.

33:37.265 --> 33:38.764
Okay...

33:38.766 --> 33:39.966
On the other side of that door

33:39.968 --> 33:41.433
is where I say goodbye.

33:41.435 --> 33:43.970
You can trust me

33:43.972 --> 33:45.805
because I'm done.

33:46.975 --> 33:51.176
There's a fishing rod
with my name on it.

33:51.178 --> 33:52.311
I just...

33:53.681 --> 33:55.447
I just...

33:55.449 --> 33:56.781
I beg you to get out too,

33:56.783 --> 33:58.417
while you still can.

34:02.389 --> 34:03.722
[Kiss]

34:05.292 --> 34:06.425
Let's go.

34:08.195 --> 34:09.393
Easy up.

34:09.396 --> 34:10.728
[Pained groan]

34:13.433 --> 34:14.632
I'll go.

34:14.635 --> 34:16.434
Forget I was ever here.

34:16.436 --> 34:18.168
And ever saw your car parked out front,

34:18.170 --> 34:21.039
that the Russians were
ever anywhere near here.

34:21.041 --> 34:24.743
I'll forget walking up
those stairs and see...

34:24.745 --> 34:26.277
[Snarling, yell of pain]

34:26.598 --> 34:30.489
[ ♪♪ ]

34:36.222 --> 34:38.489
It wasn't a dream, was it?

34:38.491 --> 34:42.726
[ ♪♪ ]

34:42.728 --> 34:44.262
That boy.

34:44.264 --> 34:46.563
He was...

34:46.565 --> 34:48.799
changing into something.

34:48.801 --> 34:50.768
[Growling]

34:50.770 --> 34:52.936
A wolf?

34:52.938 --> 34:56.406
God, did I see him change into a wolf?

34:59.111 --> 35:00.243
Yes.

35:05.984 --> 35:08.785
You saw a werewolf.

35:08.787 --> 35:12.222
That's what that boy is.

35:12.224 --> 35:14.691
And so am I.

35:14.693 --> 35:17.126
Everything you saw is real.

35:17.128 --> 35:20.329
The Russians, what happened
in this room, your leg...

35:20.331 --> 35:22.198
It's all true.

35:22.200 --> 35:24.366
And I'm still the man that you know,

35:24.368 --> 35:25.534
and I <i> am</i>

35:25.536 --> 35:29.072
just a man trying to protect his family.

35:29.074 --> 35:31.273
And you saw what we are.

35:33.878 --> 35:36.278
And you saw what I am.

35:36.280 --> 35:38.747
And no one else can know that.

35:38.749 --> 35:41.250
Can I trust you with that?

35:43.367 --> 35:44.629
[ ♪♪ ]

35:48.292 --> 35:51.227
I'm going to get you out of here. Okay?

35:52.495 --> 35:54.629
- You lost a lot of blood...
- [Gasping]

35:54.631 --> 35:56.297
You need to see a medic.

35:56.299 --> 35:57.699
[Gasp]

35:57.701 --> 36:01.870
So we're going to talk
about this another time.

36:02.773 --> 36:05.306
This is my responsibility.

36:05.308 --> 36:06.808
I'll figure it all out.

36:06.810 --> 36:08.776
- [Blade slicing through flesh]
- [Sharp gasp]

36:12.249 --> 36:14.682
[Gasping]

36:16.043 --> 36:17.844
[ ♪♪ ]

36:26.695 --> 36:28.495
[Whispering] I'm so sorry.

36:28.497 --> 36:32.099
[ ♪♪ ]

36:32.101 --> 36:34.201
I'm so sorry, Karen.

36:37.882 --> 36:39.948
[Kettle whistling]

36:39.950 --> 36:43.485
[Clattering]

36:48.195 --> 36:50.062
How's he doing?

36:50.064 --> 36:52.363
It's a good thing I got here when I did.

36:53.266 --> 36:55.700
Sepsis can get into the organs,

36:55.702 --> 36:58.703
shuts everything down.

36:58.705 --> 37:01.005
Have you tended to many werewolves?

37:01.007 --> 37:03.174
Just myself.

37:03.176 --> 37:04.642
Just once.

37:05.730 --> 37:08.413
[ ♪♪ ]

37:08.915 --> 37:11.282
Here.

37:11.284 --> 37:13.784
I was stationed in Fallujah,

37:13.786 --> 37:15.620
and there was a sniper.

37:15.622 --> 37:17.922
Pinned down a wounded
soldier in my battalion,

37:17.924 --> 37:19.123
out in the open.

37:19.125 --> 37:20.424
And if I went out to help,

37:20.426 --> 37:22.827
if I got shot and the
medics knocked me out,

37:22.829 --> 37:26.664
I wasn't sure if I'd be
able to control my Change.

37:26.666 --> 37:27.898
I could play it safe

37:27.900 --> 37:29.699
or I could do the right thing.

37:31.036 --> 37:32.836
Not really a choice.

37:32.838 --> 37:34.037
So I ran out

37:34.039 --> 37:36.240
and hauled my guy to safety.

37:36.242 --> 37:37.707
Took one in the leg.

37:38.810 --> 37:40.710
Carved it out of myself later.

37:40.712 --> 37:42.779
Did he survive?

37:42.781 --> 37:44.515
The soldier?

37:44.517 --> 37:45.649
No...

37:47.019 --> 37:49.252
But I wasn't going to let
him die out there alone.

37:53.125 --> 37:54.658
Thank you for being here.

37:54.660 --> 37:56.325
You call, I come.

37:57.428 --> 38:00.596
What would I choose that's different?

38:00.598 --> 38:02.931
We all need a purpose.

38:02.933 --> 38:05.268
Otherwise, what's the point?

38:05.270 --> 38:07.170
You're just a hitchhiker,

38:07.172 --> 38:09.004
a passenger.

38:09.006 --> 38:11.073
Not driving the bus,

38:11.075 --> 38:12.308
not choosing the path.

38:12.310 --> 38:13.509
Just, sometimes, it feels like

38:13.511 --> 38:16.679
that path is leading to a cliff.

38:16.681 --> 38:19.281
[Cellphone buzzing]

38:19.283 --> 38:21.050
I need to take this.

38:21.052 --> 38:22.517
Thank you.

38:25.522 --> 38:28.157
Are you okay? What's happening there?

38:28.159 --> 38:31.459
JEREMY: [On phone] <i>I spoke to
Jorge, he just landed in Syracuse.</i>

38:31.461 --> 38:33.395
He told me that Marsten and
Cain are on their way to you,

38:33.397 --> 38:35.363
and that you had him track Roman.

38:35.365 --> 38:38.066
He found a line of credit cards
that lead to Southern Ontario.

38:38.068 --> 38:39.501
Thank you.

38:39.503 --> 38:41.469
ELENA: <i>Are you coming back?</i>

38:42.839 --> 38:45.173
Jorge is going to come here
and clean up the room.

38:45.175 --> 38:47.909
JEREMY: <i>And he's going to bury Morgan.</i>

38:47.911 --> 38:49.244
[Sighing]

38:51.114 --> 38:52.646
Jeremy...

38:52.648 --> 38:54.115
<i>He's going to take her
car to the airport.</i>

38:54.117 --> 38:56.350
That will buy us a little bit of time

38:56.352 --> 38:59.053
before her family knows
that she's missing.

38:59.055 --> 39:00.654
And you?

39:00.656 --> 39:02.356
I'm going to go after Roman.

39:02.358 --> 39:04.025
ELENA: <i>No, you can't go by yourself.</i>

39:04.027 --> 39:06.127
Take Cain, take Clay, take me.

39:06.129 --> 39:08.495
You can't go after Roman alone.

39:08.497 --> 39:11.932
No, you have to stay there
and oversee things, Elena.

39:11.934 --> 39:13.667
I have to do this on my own.

39:15.104 --> 39:16.937
No...

39:16.939 --> 39:19.172
You are not leaving
me in charge, Jeremy!

39:19.174 --> 39:21.908
You are coming back! Please...

39:21.910 --> 39:24.778
JEREMY: <i>You know, it's fitting
that a Russian said it best.</i>

39:24.780 --> 39:26.279
<i>It was Dostoyevsky.</i>

39:26.281 --> 39:29.649
He said that "the mystery
of human existence

39:29.651 --> 39:32.185
"lies not in just staying alive...

39:33.688 --> 39:36.589
but in having something to live for."

39:38.193 --> 39:39.659
You've given me that.

39:41.329 --> 39:43.095
<i>You gave me something to fight for,</i>

39:43.097 --> 39:46.065
<i>- above and beyond just Pack rules.</i>
- [Quiet sobs]

39:46.067 --> 39:48.934
<i>And I'm not going to let Roman
take that away from me.</i>

39:48.936 --> 39:52.639
I'm not going to let him
take you away from me.

39:54.108 --> 39:56.442
[Shaky exhale]

39:56.444 --> 39:59.178
I'm going to do what
must be done, Elena.

40:01.048 --> 40:02.547
ELENA: <i>Don't hang up.</i>

40:04.886 --> 40:07.486
I forgive you, Jeremy.

40:09.323 --> 40:11.223
I forgive...

40:11.225 --> 40:13.225
<i>I forgive you.</i>

40:13.227 --> 40:14.559
[Choked sob]

40:18.265 --> 40:20.799
Thank you.

40:23.676 --> 40:26.762
[ ♪♪ ]

40:35.816 --> 40:39.951
[ ♪♪ ]

40:39.953 --> 40:41.986
No sign of the Change.

40:41.988 --> 40:44.155
Looks like an animal attack.

40:44.157 --> 40:46.791
We'll leave the body here
for someone to find.

40:46.793 --> 40:49.193
Let his loved ones have some closure.

40:52.030 --> 40:54.663
[ ♪♪ ]

40:58.471 --> 41:00.771
It was the wolf in me.

41:02.041 --> 41:05.675
The wolf was excited to attack this guy.

41:05.677 --> 41:07.211
Trevor.

41:07.213 --> 41:09.813
Feeling that adrenaline rush...

41:09.815 --> 41:11.949
it was unbelievable.

41:14.920 --> 41:17.387
What if that's who I am?

41:17.389 --> 41:18.989
What if I can't stop?

41:23.500 --> 41:25.598
[ ♪♪ ]

41:28.933 --> 41:30.533
SONJA: [On voicemail] <i>Hey, babe!</i>

41:30.535 --> 41:32.569
<i>Sorry for bitching about my mom.</i>

41:32.571 --> 41:34.637
<i>She's bringing salad.</i>

41:34.639 --> 41:36.805
<i>Did you move the deck
chairs to the cottage?</i>

41:36.807 --> 41:38.341
<i>They're not in the shed.</i>

41:38.343 --> 41:39.742
[Chuckling]

41:39.744 --> 41:41.010
<i>I am the worst.</i>

41:41.012 --> 41:43.112
<i>Bothering you while you're out there,</i>

41:43.114 --> 41:44.646
<i>keeping the deer away,</i>

41:44.648 --> 41:46.415
<i>making sure no one else
loses a kid brother</i>

41:46.417 --> 41:48.384
<i>to a stray bullet.</i>

41:48.386 --> 41:49.718
<i>I love you.</i>

41:51.222 --> 41:55.027
[ ♪♪ ]

42:06.236 --> 42:09.658
[ ♪♪ ]

42:19.316 --> 42:20.916
CLAY: Elena!

42:28.958 --> 42:32.560
[ ♪♪ ]

42:32.562 --> 42:34.128
[Mouthing silently]

42:34.793 --> 42:37.238
[ ♪♪ ]

42:38.301 --> 42:39.500
Every one of us

42:39.502 --> 42:41.869
gets to this place in a different way.

42:42.939 --> 42:43.938
We need each other.

42:43.940 --> 42:45.839
It's the only way we can do this.

42:45.841 --> 42:48.309
I'll get him under control.

42:49.278 --> 42:50.477
What about my father?

42:50.479 --> 42:52.846
He's resting upstairs.

42:52.848 --> 42:54.315
He's been through a lot as well

42:54.317 --> 42:55.950
and he could use your
strength right now.

43:04.225 --> 43:06.025
I found this at the front gate.

43:16.804 --> 43:18.371
[Device clicks into computer]

43:20.308 --> 43:22.308
Jeremy called.

43:22.310 --> 43:23.642
Morgan.

43:25.280 --> 43:26.612
She saw.

43:27.949 --> 43:31.050
Jorge is on his way, he'll handle it.

43:32.386 --> 43:34.887
Jeremy's gone after Roman.

43:34.889 --> 43:36.054
Where?

43:36.056 --> 43:38.222
I don't now. He demanded
we not follow him.

43:38.224 --> 43:39.491
But we have to go.

43:39.493 --> 43:43.427
[Fighting yells and groans on video]

43:43.429 --> 43:45.497
[Groan, cough]

43:47.100 --> 43:49.634
- [Impact, screaming]
- It's Marsten.

43:50.704 --> 43:52.637
[Yelling in pain]

43:52.639 --> 43:55.339
MARSTEN: [On video] <i>Please, enough!
Enough!</i>

